SatOps
------
Ruby tool with commands to manipulate and automate Red Hat Satellite objects using its XML/RPC API interface


REQUIREMENTS
------------
- Ruby versions
  We have tested
  - 1.8.7p358
  - 1.9.3p194
  - 2.0.0p247

- Red Hat (Network) Satellite versions
  - RHN Satellite 5.4.1 with latest updates
  - RHN Satellite 5.5
  - RH Satellite 5.6


INSTALL
-------
gem install satops


QUICKSTART
----------
1 - Generate source and target satellites definition file
2 - Generate configuration file
3 - Launch satops. For instance to sync a target satellite from a source

./satops.rb show sat > satellites.yaml
./satops.rb show config > config.yaml
./satops.rb -s satellites.yaml -c config.yaml sync


MANUAL
------
For a short version help, run satops without option
For more details, please refer to the included MANUAL


DEVELOPMENTS
------------
- Due to the continuing development efforts of the RH Satellite engineering
  team the API is changing over time to include fixes and enhancement.


